@startuml diagram-bruin-run3-fail
scale 1.5
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #e3f2fd
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #1565c0

title Run 3: What Happens When a Quality Check Fails?

start
:We edit raw_reviews.sql:\nremove **5** from accepted_values\nso the check becomes [1, 2, 3, 4];

:**raw_reviews**\nTable created successfully\n(the SQL itself ran fine);
note right
  **Quality checks**
  rating: not_null  ✓
  rating: accepted_values [1,2,3,4]  **FAIL**
  //reviews with rating=5 exist//
  //but 5 is no longer in the list//
  review_date: not_null  ✓
end note

:**monthly_summary: UPSTREAM FAILED**\nBruin refuses to run it\nbecause raw_reviews failed a check;
note right
  The quality gate caught a problem
  **before** it reached the summary.

  In a folder-of-scripts world,
  the summary would silently
  compute on bad data.
end note
stop

@enduml
